column5: Notes  Put your column headings into the third column of the appropriate row.  Do not edit the first column.  Save as a CSV file
Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) expressed as microseconds since midnight (00:00:00), January 1, 1970. (Unix time stamp multiplied by one million)
Descriptive Mission Identifier to distinguish event or sortie. Value field is Free Text. Maximum 127 characters.
Identifier of platform. Value field is Free Text. Maximum 127 characters.
Aircraft heading relative to True North, measured clockwise in the horizontal plane looking down.  Compass direction, range 0.0 to 360.0
Aircraft pitch relative to horizontal plane with positive angles for nose above the horizontal plane.
Platform roll angle relative to horizontal plane with positive angles for left wing above the horizontal plane.
True airspeed (TAS) of platform. Indicated Airspeed adjusted for temperature and altitude.
Indicated airspeed (IAS) of platform. Derived from Pitot tube and static pressure sensors.
Use Platform Designation String . Value field is Free Text. Maximum 127 characters.
String of image source sensor. Value field is Free Text. Maximum 127 characters.
String of the image coordinate system used. E.g.: 'Geodetic WGS84'
Sensor Latitude. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid.  Range -90.0 to 90.0
Sensor Longitude. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Range -180.0 to 180.0
Altitude of sensor as measured from Mean Sea Level (MSL).
Horizontal field of view of selected imaging sensor.
Vertical field of view of selected imaging sensor.
Relative angle of sensor pointing direction to platform longitudinal axis as seen from above the platform. Compass direction, range 0.0 to 360.0
Relative angle of sensor pointing dhirection to the platform horizontal plane. Negative angles down.
Relative roll angle of sensor to aircraft platform. Top of image level is zero degrees. Positive angles are clockwise when looking from behind camera.
Slant range in meters. Distance to center of frame.
Target Width within sensor field of view.
Latitude of frame center. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Range -90.0 to 90.0
Longitude of frame center. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Range -180.0 to 180.0
Terrain elevation at frame center relative to Mean Sea Level (MSL).
Frame Latitude, offset for upper left corner. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Use with Frame Center Latitude.
Frame Longitude, offset for upper left corner. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Use with Frame Center Longitude.
Frame Latitude, offset for upper right corner. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Use with Frame Center Latitude.
Frame Longitude, offset for upper right corner. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Use with Frame Center Longitude.
Frame Latitude, offset for lower right corner. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Use with Frame Center Latitude.
Frame Longitude, offset for lower right corner. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Use with Frame Center Longitude.
Frame Latitude, offset for lower left corner. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Use with Frame Center Latitude.
Frame Longitude, offset for lower left corner. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid. Use with Frame Center Longitude.
Flag for icing detected at aircraft location.
Wind direction at aircraft location. This is the direction the wind is coming from relative to true north.
Wind speed at aircraft location.
Static pressure at aircraft location.
Density altitude at aircraft location.
Temperature outside of aircraft.
Calculated Target latitude. This is the crosshair location if different from frame center. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid.
Calculated Target longitude. This is the crosshair location if different from frame center. Based on WGS84 ellipsoid.
Calculated target elevation. This is the crosshair location if different from frame center.
Tracking gate width (x value) of tracked target within field of view. Closely tied to source video resolution in pixels.
Tracking gate height (y value) of tracked target within field of view. Closely tied to source video resolution in pixels.
Circular Error 90 (CE90) is the estimated error distance in the horizontal direction.
Lateral Error 90 (LE90) is the estimated error distance in the vertical (or lateral) direction.
Generic Flagged Metadata Position Format
Differential pressure at aircraft location.
Platform Attack Angle. Angle between platform longitudinal axis and relative wind. Positive angles for upward relative wind.
Vertical speed of the aircraft relative to zenith. Positive ascending, negative descending.
The sideslip angle is the angle between the platform longitudinal axis and relative wind. Positive angles to right wing, neg to left.
Local pressure at airfield of known height.
Elevation of Airfield corresponding to Airfield Barometric Pressure.
Relative Humidity at aircraft location.
Speed projected to the ground of an airborne platform passing overhead.
Horizontal distance from ground position of aircraft relative to nadir. Dependent upon Slant Range and Depression Angle.
Remaining fuel on airborne platform. Metered as fuel weight remaining.
Call Sign of platform or operating unit. Value field is Free Text.
Codes for current weapons stored on aircraft
Indication when a particular weapon is released.
A laser's Pulse Repetition Frequency (PRF) code
Name for sensor field of view setting
Aircraft heading  relative to Magnetic North, measured clockwise in the horizontal plane. Compass direction, range 0.0 to 360.0
Version number of the UAS LS document used to generate a source of UAS LS KLV metadata.
Alternate Platform Latitude.
Alternate Platform Longitude.
Altitude of alternate platform as measured from Mean Sea Level (MSL).
Name of alternate platform connected to UAS.
Heading angle of alternate platform connected to UAS.
Start time expressed as microseconds elapsed since midnight (00:00:00), January 1, 1970.

Video Moving Target Indicator MISB STD0903, expressed in series of objects, with each object separate by ';' and each of following data fieleds separated by space [id, confidence level, image pixel# for top left, image pixel# for bottom right, center image pixel#;id ..]
Sensor Ellipsoid Height as measured from the reference WGS84 Ellipsoid.
Alternate Platform Ellipsoid Height as measured from the reference WGS84 Ellipsoid.
Indicates the mode of operations of the event portrayed in metadata.
Frame Center Ellipsoid Height as measured from the reference WGS84 Ellipsoid.
Northing velocity of the sensor or platform. Positive towards True North
Easting velocity of the sensor or platform. Positive towards East.
